# bm-klus-bv.nl — site-wide rules

Project-specific guardrails that always apply. Full governance in `docs/governance/`.
For the deeper canonical lists see also `00-always.mdc` and `CLAUDE.md`.

## Content & language
- Public-facing content is **Dutch (nl-NL) only**. No Russian or English on public pages.
- Do not create empty or placeholder pages.
- Do not make unconfirmed claims.
- Never invent reviews, guarantees, savings percentages, exact lead times, subsidies, certifications, or legal facts.
- For uncertainty use flags: `[CLAIM_NEEDS_CONFIRMATION]`, `[MISSING_BUSINESS_INPUT]`, `[UNCERTAIN_TERM]`.
- Energy-savings wording stays conditional: "kan leiden tot", never "leidt tot".

## SEO limits (hard)
- meta title ≤ 60 characters
- meta description ≤ 160 characters
- slug ≤ 75 characters
- All URLs use a trailing slash.

## Project pages
- Keep a factual case-description tone. No generic sales copy.
- `relatedLinks` point only to service pages.
- Preserve existing content/schema/router helpers — only narrow, requested changes.

## Architecture
- Preserve the static-first Next.js architecture (App Router, `output: 'export'`, static export to `out/`).
- Prefer Server / static components. Do not add `"use client"` without a real interactive need.
- Do not add heavy dependencies casually.
- Do not assume Node/npm exists on Antagonist hosting at request time.
- Do not rebuild deployment architecture.
- Do not change the WordPress MU-plugin backend unless the task is explicitly about backend / contact / stats endpoints.

## Integrations — do not casually change
- Consent Mode v2
- CookieScript
- GTM
- GA4
- Google Search Console wiring
- Google Ads
- Cloudflare Turnstile (and contact-form honeypot, WP REST endpoint, `wp_mail` flow)

Touch any of the above only when the task explicitly requests it.

## Tooling
- Package manager is **pnpm** only (not npm, not yarn).
- `pnpm lint` will fail (ESLint not installed). Use `npx tsc --noEmit` for verification.
